(42, 15, 5, 33, 7, 18, 18, 'layeth it on his shoulders, rejoicing', 'Connection of Mercy and Joy', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy in mercy. In Luke, the shepherd rejoices upon finding the lost sheep, paralleling Micah''s emphasis on God''s delight in mercy and forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 15, 5, 42, 19, 9, 9, 'rejoicing', 'Salvation and Rejoicing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy in salvation. In both passages, the act of finding and rejoicing parallels the declaration of salvation to Zacchaeus, emphasizing the joy associated with being restored and recognized as part of God''s people.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 15, 5, 26, 18, 23, 23, 'rejoicing', 'Joy in Redemption', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejoicing in the return of the lost. Both passages emphasize the desire for the wicked to return and live, paralleling the joy expressed in finding the lost sheep.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
